The tech space is crowded, but most solutions feel like they’re cut from the same cloth — missing the mark on what businesses truly need. Organizations are chasing innovation, but too often, it comes at the expense of flexibility, independence, and real technological depth. At Dawn Technologies is a niche company laser-focused on delivering specialized tech solutions in Gen AI, Data Engineering, and Backend Systems. What sets us apart is our commitment to the technologists — the creators, problem-solvers, and innovators who bring true value to transformation. 
We believe that teamwork plus talent equals exceptional results. We are looking for teammates who are great problem solvers and enjoy collaborating within a team to achieve big outcomes. 

Job Description: 

Must-Have Requirements

Strong Python Skills:
From 7 to 10 years of experience with python programming.
Solid understanding of Python’s object-oriented features, decorators, and packaging.
Practical proficiency in using design patterns (abstraction, factory, adapter, façade, iterator, etc,…) and creating reusable code modules.
Good Expertise on automated test definition and implementation.
Containerization & Orchestration:
Familiarity with containerizing FASTAPI applications (e.g., Docker) and deploying them to orchestration platforms like Kubernetes.
FASTAPI Proficiency:
Ability to develop and maintain complex FASTAPI applications, including authentication and secure inter-endpoint communications.
Capability to extend FASTAPI via custom classes, decorators, or plugins.
API Security best practices
LangChain/LangGraph Knowledge:
Hands-on experience creating and managing agents within LangChain or LangGraph.
Ability to incorporate telemetry (OpenTelemetry or similar) and leverage callbacks or library modifications.
Asynchronous Programming:
Familiarity with async/await patterns and concurrency in Python.
Understanding of how to structure code to be performant and maintainable for asynchronous tasks.

Nice-to-Have Requirements

Additional Agentic Frameworks/Tools
Prior experience with frameworks such as OpenAI API, Autogen, Google ADK, or other agentic libraries.
MCP Server Creation Experience
Exposure to or willingness to learn advanced server topics like MCP.
Data Engineering for Telemetry Logs
Knowledgeable in structuring or processing telemetry data pipelines, logs, or distributed tracing systems.

Benefits & Perks: 

Competitive, performance-based compensation. 

Comprehensive healthcare benefits (medical). 

Generous paid time off and flexible leave policies. 

Access to learning & development resources (courses, certifications). 

A culture centered on innovation, excellence, and growth. 

At AT Dawn Technologies, we believe in creating a workplace where innovation, ownership, and excellence thrive. We are proud to be an equal-opportunity employer that celebrates diversity and inclusion. 
 
Come join us and help redefine the future! 

 ', 0, 10, '{}', 'draft', 'e2cf3e7b-d16b-49c7-9a60-00e65ec3049e', 'e2cf3e7b-d16b-49c7-9a60-00e65ec3049e', NULL, NULL, '2025-09-06 18:53:39.568349+00', '2025-09-06 18:53:39.568349+00'),
	('557113b6-0a66-4ab1-9b9e-b4c637edb5a4', 'Senior Architect for Hybrid Cloud', 'Engineering', 'Mumbai,Bangalore', 'full_time', 'About At Dawn Technologies

The tech space is crowded, but most solutions feel like they’re cut from the same cloth—missing the mark on what businesses truly need. Organizations are chasing innovation, but too often, it comes at the expense of flexibility, independence, and real technological depth. AT Dawn Technologies is a niche company which is laser-focused on delivering specialized tech solutions in Gen AI, Data Engineering, and Backend Systems. What sets us apart is our commitment to technologists— the creators, problem-solvers, and innovators who bring true value to transformation. We believe that teamwork plus talent equals exceptional results and, as such, are looking for teammates that are great problem solvers and enjoy collaborating within a team to achieve big outcomes.

Role Overview

We’re looking for a Cloud Solutions Architect who knows their way around multi-cloud and hybrid environments like the back of their hand. In this role, you’ll design scalable, secure, and cost-efficient architectures across AWS, Azure, and on-prem setups. You’ll lead complex migrations and repatriation projects, optimize cloud spend, and make sure everything is running smoothly—and securely. Bonus points if you’re familiar with HP PCE, Veeam, or VMware. Strong communication skills are a must since you’ll be working closely with tech teams, leadership, and clients. If you’ve got 8+ years of experience, a knack for translating technical speak into business value, and thrive in a hybrid environment (3 days in office, 2 remote), we’d love to hear from you!

Key Responsibilities:

Cloud Architecture & Design:
Develop and design scalable, secure, and cost-efficient multi-cloud and hybrid cloud architectures aligned with diverse business requirements.
Establish processes and policies for infrastructure design, build, and implementation.
Enterprise Infrastructure Expertise:
Demonstrate a deep understanding of enterprise-level infrastructure, including Compute, Storage, Networking, Security, Observability, and Resiliency (HA, Backup, DR).
Possess a strong grasp of Private, Public, and Hybrid Cloud infrastructure strategies, with expertise in AWS, Azure, and On-Premise environments.
Basic understanding of HP Private Cloud Enterprise (PCE) concepts.
Migration & Re-patriation Leadership:
Plan, schedule, and lead complex cloud migration and re-patriation initiatives.
Lead execution teams through various solution delivery phases, including repatriation, migration, and new builds.
Cost Optimization & Performance Enhancement:
Analyze and understand cloud billing (including PCE) to identify cost-saving opportunities.
Plan and execute audits and optimization efforts to reduce cloud spending, advising on the effective use of Reserved Instances (RI), Savings Plans (SP), or Spot Instances.
Recommend and implement solutions to optimize operating costs and enhance application and infrastructure performance for customers.
Security & Compliance:
Ensure all cloud environments adhere to industry security standards and compliance requirements.
Communication & Stakeholder Management:
Lead and facilitate technical conversations between core infrastructure and other IT teams.
Review new product offerings from a customer-centric perspective.
Prepare clear MIS and status reports for senior management.
Document technical details and processes thoroughly.
Leverage strong business acumen to foster and grow client engagements in collaboration with sales and delivery teams.

Required Skills & Experience:

8+ years experience as an solutions architect
Proven experience in Cloud Architecture and design with a strong understanding of Azure and AWS cloud platforms.
Expertise in Repatriation and Migration strategies, execution.
Hands-on experience of HP PCE, VMware, NSX-T, and Backup Solutions (e.g., Veeam).
Familiarity with OpsRamp and GL Metering.
Excellent Communication skills (written and verbal).
Nutanix and Hyperconverged Infrastructure (HCI)
Pursuit Experience (experience in pre-sales, solutioning, or proposal development is highly valued).
This position is hybrid with 3 days mandatory in the office and 2 working remotely.', 7, 15, '{}', 'draft', 'e2cf3e7b-d16b-49c7-9a60-00e65ec3049e', 'e2cf3e7b-d16b-49c7-9a60-00e65ec3049e', NULL, NULL, '2025-09-07 19:16:30.486863+00', '2025-09-07 19:16:30.486863+00');


