Strengths observed

17+ yrs across DC & cloud with presales/solutioning leadership; comfortable translating business needs and owning delivery conversations. Resume shows broad DC modernization, virtualization, storage/backup/DR, and public cloud exposure (AWS/Azure/GCP). 

HCI/Nutanix exposure and multi-site work; has operated in RFP/BOM/architecture-doc motions and led teams—useful for our enterprise engagements. 

Motivation & ownership: Clear appetite to diversify and step up; good customer presence.

Gaps to validate in a tech deep-dive

Hybrid strategy & landing zones: Want concrete designs using Azure CAF, RBAC/policy, hub-spoke, ExpressRoute/Arc governance, and AVS where appropriate. Today’s call didn’t reach that level of specificity. 

Kubernetes platform design: Expect on-prem (Tanzu/OpenShift) + AKS patterns, GitOps (Argo/Flux), HPA/PDBs, service mesh, and observability choices. Not evidenced yet. 

IaC & DevOps: Terraform module structure, state/policy as code, pipelines (ADO/GitHub), config mgmt (Ansible) and drift handling—need hands-on examples. 

DR & security posture: ASR/AVS options, runbooks, drill cadence; unified IAM (AAD/Conditional Access), Defender/SIEM, container security. 

Answer hygiene: Tendency to be long-winded; needs crisper, decision-grade responses under estimation/sizing probes.

Risk/Logistics

Notice period stated as 90 days (maybe 60); buyout unlikely. Plan timelines accordingly.

Recommendation 
Run a 60-minute internal deep-dive with Michael or Mohan. Use the following sections (each tied to our rubric/reference):

Hybrid design case (on-prem VMware + Azure): Draw HLD covering CAF landing zones, Arc governance, AVS vs native, hub-spoke, ExpressRoute, and cost/risk trade-offs. 

K8s platform: On-prem + AKS node-pool strategy, storage classes, network policies, GitOps, upgrade/rollback, and SLOs/observability. 

IaC & CI/CD: Walk through Terraform module layout, state/backends, policy-as-code, and an ADO/GitHub pipeline with security gates. 

DR/Security: ASR runbook, quarterly drills, Sentinel/Defender, secrets/IAM patterns. 

HCI/Nutanix lens (10 min): Where he’d pick Nutanix (AHV/Prism/Flow/Calm) vs 3-tier; sizing & DR considerations. 

My call: Proceed to the internal deep-dive (I expect him to do well with preparation). If he demonstrates the specifics above, green-light client interviews;', 'submitted', '2025-09-07 19:19:51.227068+00', '2025-09-07 19:38:06.379775+00'),
